Healthy growth in disbursements, resilient asset quality and better than expected net profit (adjusted for one-offs) outlined LIC Housing Finance March  quarter (Q4) results. However, the net profit stood at Rs 378 crore was impacted by a one-time provision towards deferred tax liability to comply with National Housing Bank (NHB) norms. Adjusting for this amount of Rs 31 crore, net profit stood at Rs 409 crore, which is 4.6 per cent ahead of the consensus Bloomberg estimate of Rs 391 crore. Not surprisingly, the LIC Housing Finance stock gained almost a per cent on a day when the S&amp;P BSE Sensex was down nearly two per cent. Notably, analysts remain bullish on the company’s prospects and expect more gains in the counter.&#13;
