	The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) is working on creating a single point distribution system for all securities market benefits.This means that all the cash that you receive from your security market activities including dividends, interest income from securities as well as redemption proceeds will all be distributed by the same agency. &#13;
&#13;
	A consultation paper on allowing depositories to act as the single point of contact for these benefits is likely to be released soon, according to the minutes of the regulator's March 22nd Board meeting.ALSO READ: Tech M, NSE arms among niche bank applicants"World over, in most developed markets and several emerging markets depositories usually distribute cash benefits to their accountholders...It is proposed to have a detailed consultation process with concerned market participants on the issue of considering a mechanism where in all securities related benefits can be distributed at a single point," it said.ALSO READ: Govt slashes dividend payment estimates from banks, FIs for FY15Depositories only distribute non-cash benefits currently including bonus and rights issues, by which shares are credited to the investor's account. Cash benefits are currently distributed through Registrar and Share Transfer Agents (RTAs such as Karvy or CAMS).&#13;
&#13;
	&#13;
	Issuers too distribute cash benefits themselves by making arrangements after obtaining information from the depositories. Global depositories often hold a restricted banking license in order that they may process cash benefits directly.&#13;
