“The problem of complaints regarding dividends is also on account of incomplete information regarding investors’ financial details. A significant number of investors are yet to fully update their bank account details. This will have to be addressed for the problems associated with dividend distribution to be solved with finality,” said Ganapathy Subramanian, advisor to RTA Karvy Computershare.“So far as the systems are simplified, it is a good measure. Investors don’t have to write to multiple entities if there is a problem,” said Prakash Shah, secretary of Investor Education and Welfare Association.

